cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper deals with mobile visual search systems, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques for image processing and retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves client-server architecture and mobile devices, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of similarity functions and feature representations for retrieval could also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for improving user interaction and mobile usability, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
